{{Infobox organization |name = Institute of Food and Radiation Biology |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1974 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Savar Upazila|Savar]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [www.aere.org.bd/IFRB/ifrb.html Institute of Food and Radiation Biology] |remarks = }}
'''Institute of Food and Radiation Biology''' is a government research institute that studies food preservation methods through irradiation.<ref name="dxs">{{cite web|last1=Haque|first1=Miah Md Sirajul|title=Institute of Food and Radiation Biology|url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Institute_of_Food_and_Radiation_Biology|website=en.banglapedia.org|publisher=Banglapedia|accessdate=27 April 2017|language=en}}</ref> The institute is part of the [[Bangladesh Atomic Energy Commission]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Phillips|first1=G. O.|last2=Kearn|first2=J. N.|last3=Strong|first3=D. M.|last4=Versen|first4=R. Von|last5=Nather|first5=A.|title=Advances in Tissue Banking|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NEZqDQAAQBAJ&pg=PA400&dq=Institute+of+Food+and+Radiation+Biology&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwidgLHk8cPTAhUH1oMKHc6uAIAQ6AEIKzAB#v=onepage&q=Institute%20of%20Food%20and%20Radiation%20Biology&f=false|website=400|publisher=World Scientific|accessdate=27 April 2017|language=en|date=1 January 1999}}</ref>
==History== The institute was established on 1974 as the Irradiation and Pest Control Research Institute. In 1979 the institute was moved to Atomic Energy Research Establishment and renamed Institute of Food and Radiation Biology. The institute has an irradiation facility that offers its services at subsidized rate to Bangladeshi companies.<ref name="dxs" /> The institute has a Cobalt-60 gamma irradiator that is operated by the Gamma Source Division.<ref>{{cite web|title=Making food safer and longer-lasting|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/making-food-safer-and-longer-lasting|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=27 April 2017|language=en|date=17 May 2013}}</ref>
